    "The term \"input layer\" denotes the layer in a neural network closest to the input data, while the term \"output layer\" denotes the layer closest to the output.",
    "The term \"hidden layers\" pertains to the intermediate layers between the observable layers.",
    "DNNs have demonstrated their ability to effectively address complex problems such as image classification, natural language processing (NLP), and speech recognition.",
